illegal in china but quite common and often disguised as massage. most hot spring or sauna establishments offer all the services a businessman might want for relaxation. as for the smaller places, if you see pink lighting or lots of girls in short skirts, probably considerably more than just massage is on offer, and quite often they cannot do a good massage. the same rule applies in many hair salons which double as massage parlors/brothels. the non-pink-lit places usually give good massage and generally do not offer sex. if the establishment advertises massage by the blind, it is almost certain 